    "body": "Quick thoughts: Why call it `listen` rather than also calling it `on` and just allowing the omission of the callback?  Hell, we can go one step further -- why not just have `instance.func().transactionHash`, `instance.func().receipt`, etc, each as promises, eliminating the use of strings?  This does create some limitations (you can't give an event the same name as a field or method of  PromiEvent, or rather this new extension class), but, I still think it's preferable to strings.",
